headline: Is News Corp (NWSA) Offering Value After Recent Share Price Slump?
summary: If you are wondering whether News is starting to look interesting at its current share price, this article will walk through what the recent moves might mean for value focused investors. The stock last closed at US$22.74, with a 7 day return of a 15.1% decline, a 30 day return of a 14.1% decline, a year to date return of a 13.2% decline and a 1 year return of a 21.5% decline, while the 3 year and 5 year returns sit at 23.7% and 0.3% respectively. headline: 3 S&P 500 Stocks We’re Skeptical Of
summary: While the S&P 500 (^GSPC) includes industry leaders, not every stock in the index is a winner. Some companies are past their prime, weighed down by poor execution, weak financials, or structural headwinds.
